Grant recipients in many parts of KwaZulu-Natal haven't been paid. This is due to technical problems and delays in the Sassa system. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Grant recipients in many parts of KwaZulu-Natal haven't been paid. This is due to technical problems and delays in the Sassa system. Thousands of beneficiaries went to over-crowded places on Monday only to leave empty-handed. Sassa admits to the faults in its system. SA lockdown: Sassa glitch causes delay in grant payments But no one seems to know the nature and cause of the technical glitch. “The only information that was shared with us is that there is a technical glitch. Which is what we’ve been communicating with our beneficiaries and we know that they are in control and would ensure that everything us one accordingly to ensure that atlas our beneficiaries get paid and indeed we received good news that the issue has been resolved,” Godlwana added. Those at payout points say payment days are a challenge, especially when trying to comply with lockdown regulations. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.